@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnFormDemo — Phase 7.3 Task 1.3 (design §"The proof surface"), route
    "/form", mount-registry key "BnFormDemo". Authored in .razor.

    A SEVENTH page, same rationale as the fourth through sixth: the existing
    pages' frame tables and goldens ARE the parity contracts, and the phase
    that makes the form controls real does not get to rewrite them. This
    page's numbers are ITS OWN contract — asserted by BnFormDemoTests (the
    .NET golden) and by Gates 2/3 on the AVD and the iOS simulator.

    ── THE PAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    Each control TWICE — a BOUND instance (the live @bind- pair) and a
    DISABLED one (fixed state, Enabled=false) — inside one BnColumn, then a
    summary BnText echoing the whole bound state (the multi-control bind
    proof: ANY control's round-trip re-renders the echo), then the back row.

      [0] BnCheckbox  bound     @bind-Checked  (initially false)
      [1] BnCheckbox  disabled  Checked=true
      [2] BnSwitch    bound     @bind-Checked  (initially true)
      [3] BnSwitch    disabled  Checked=true
      [4] BnSlider    bound     @bind-Value    (25; 0..100 step 5; W=240)
      [5] BnSlider    disabled  Value=50       (0..100, continuous; W=240)
      [6] BnPicker    bound     @bind-SelectedIndex (0 of Alpha/Bravo/Charlie; W=240)
      [7] BnPicker    disabled  SelectedIndex=1                            (W=240)
      [8] the echo    BnText — EchoText below, invariant, wire-cased bools
      [9] back row    BnRow W=300 → BnButton "← Back"

    ── DECLARED vs INTRINSIC (design §Measurement — the 6.1 law) ────────────
    Sizes are DECLARED wherever a number is asserted CROSS-platform: the
    sliders and pickers carry Width=240 (a slider's intrinsic width is an
    arbitrary platform constant no two platforms share — declaring it is what
    makes "the slider is 240dp wide" one assertion on both shells). The
    checkboxes and switches deliberately declare NOTHING: their sizes are the
    platforms' own intrinsics (a UISwitch is 51×31pt, a MaterialCheckBox is
    whatever Material says), asserted PER-platform against the platform's own
    measurement (the 6.3 oracle method) — frame parity applies to LAYOUT,
    never to intrinsic control sizes.

    ── WHAT THE THREE SURFACES ASSERT ───────────────────────────────────────
    .NET golden: the creates (2 each of NodeTypes 8/9/10 + 2 pickers), the
    full prop tables (values, min/max/step, the items JSON, the clamped
    selectedIndex, enabled on the disabled four), the attach count (NINE —
    all eight controls attach change, disabled included [BnFormControlTests'
    recorded decision], + the back click), and the four bind round-trips
    through the production dispatch ingress re-rendering the echo.
    On-device (Gates 2/3): toggle/slide/pick each BOUND control → the echo
    re-renders; programmatic set re-fires nothing (the loop guard, VERIFIED
    per control); the picker clamp; DISABLED CONTROLS DISPATCH NOTHING (the
    on-device half of the disabled-attach decision); the declared 240/300
    widths in the frames.

    Nav parity with every other page: "← Back" → INavigationManager → "/".
    Reachable by mount-name ("BnFormDemo") and by route ("/form"); no button
    on BnDemo points here (adding one would churn BnDemo's goldens for no
    engine reason). A fresh ROOT component: no cascaded theme crosses a root
    swap. Android's DEEP_LINK_COMPONENTS line is Gate 2's.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnColumn>
    @* [0]/[1] the checkbox pair — INTRINSIC size on purpose (see header). *@
    <BnCheckbox @bind-Checked="_checked" />
    <BnCheckbox Checked="@DisabledCheckboxChecked" Enabled="false" />

    @* [2]/[3] the switch pair — same wire as the checkbox, NodeType 9 vs 8
       (and on iOS the same UISwitch: the recorded decision-2 divergence). *@
    <BnSwitch @bind-Checked="_switched" />
    <BnSwitch Checked="@DisabledSwitchChecked" Enabled="false" />

    @* [4]/[5] the slider pair — Width DECLARED (240): the one axis a number
       is asserted cross-platform. The bound one is stepped (5), the disabled
       one continuous — both prop shapes on one page. *@
    <BnSlider @bind-Value="_slider" Min="@SliderMin" Max="@SliderMax" Step="@SliderStep"
              Width="@ControlWidth" />
    <BnSlider Value="@DisabledSliderValue" Min="@SliderMin" Max="@SliderMax"
              Enabled="false" Width="@ControlWidth" />

    @* [6]/[7] the picker pair — the SAME three items on both (one items JSON
       literal for every surface to pin), selection 0 bound / 1 disabled. *@
    <BnPicker Items="@PickerItems" @bind-SelectedIndex="_selected" Width="@ControlWidth" />
    <BnPicker Items="@PickerItems" SelectedIndex="@DisabledPickerIndex" Enabled="false"
              Width="@ControlWidth" />

    @* [8] the echo — the multi-control bind proof. Its text is the page's
       bound state, formatted by ONE function all surfaces read. *@
    <BnText Text="@EchoText" />

    @* [9] nav parity — the page's only measured leaf, LAST (a font-dependent
       height must not sit above anything a frame assertion depends on). *@
    <BnRow Width="@BackRowWidth">
        <BnButton Label="← Back" OnClick="GoBack" />
    </BnRow>
</BnColumn>

@code {
    // ── THE PAGE'S NUMBERS, AS CONSTANTS (the BnScrollDemo discipline) ────────
    //
    // BnFormDemoTests asserts these off the WIRE (never transcribed), and
    // Gates 2/3 read them for the device assertions — one source of truth.

    /// <summary>The declared control width — sliders and pickers (see the
    /// header: declared where asserted cross-platform; a slider's intrinsic
    /// width is an arbitrary platform constant).</summary>
    internal const int ControlWidthDp = 240;

    /// <summary>The back row's declared width — every page's nav row shape.</summary>
    internal const int BackRowWidthDp = 300;

    /// <summary>The bound slider's range and step — DECLARED on the wire.</summary>
    internal const float SliderMin = 0f;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="SliderMin"/>
    internal const float SliderMax = 100f;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="SliderMin"/>
    internal const float SliderStep = 5f;

    /// <summary>The bound controls' INITIAL state — what the mount golden and
    /// the first device screenshot show, and what <see cref="EchoText"/>
    /// starts from.</summary>
    internal const bool InitialChecked = false;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="InitialChecked"/>
    internal const bool InitialSwitched = true;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="InitialChecked"/>
    internal const float InitialSliderValue = 25f;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="InitialChecked"/>
    internal const int InitialSelectedIndex = 0;

    /// <summary>The disabled instances' fixed state — visibly ON/mid-range/
    /// second item, so a disabled control is distinguishable from a default
    /// one in every screenshot.</summary>
    internal const bool DisabledCheckboxChecked = true;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="DisabledCheckboxChecked"/>
    internal const bool DisabledSwitchChecked = true;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="DisabledCheckboxChecked"/>
    internal const float DisabledSliderValue = 50f;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="DisabledCheckboxChecked"/>
    internal const int DisabledPickerIndex = 1;

    /// <summary>Both pickers' items. THE wire literal every surface pins is
    /// <c>["Alpha","Bravo","Charlie"]</c> (the BnItemsJson grammar). Plain
    /// ASCII on purpose — the grammar's torture cases live in
    /// BnItemsJsonTests, not in a page humans read in screenshots.</summary>
    internal static readonly IReadOnlyList<string> PickerItems = ["Alpha", "Bravo", "Charlie"];

    /// <summary>The echo line, formatted ONCE for every surface: invariant
    /// numbers (a Dutch device must echo "sl:62.5", never "62,5") and
    /// wire-cased bools ("true"/"false" — the same casing the change payloads
    /// carry, so a device assertion reads one vocabulary).</summary>
    internal static string Echo(bool check, bool sw, float slider, int picker)
        => string.Create(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture,
            $"cb:{(check ? "true" : "false")} sw:{(sw ? "true" : "false")} sl:{slider} pk:{picker}");

    private bool _checked = InitialChecked;
    private bool _switched = InitialSwitched;
    private float _slider = InitialSliderValue;
    private int _selected = InitialSelectedIndex;

    private string EchoText => Echo(_checked, _switched, _slider, _selected);

    private static readonly string ControlWidth =
        ControlWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string BackRowWidth =
        BackRowWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    private Task GoBack() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/").AsTask();
}
